summary:
The Security Council,

Recalling previous resolutions on Lebanon and the situation in Lebanon, 
Recalling the Convention on the Safety of United Nations and Associated Personnel, 
Having studied the report of the Secretary-General on the United Nations Interim Force in Lebanon, 
Welcoming efforts by the United Nations to sensitize peacekeeping personnel on HIV/AIDS and other communicable diseases, 

1. Decides to extend the mandate of the United Nations Interim Force in Lebanon for six months, until 31 July 2000; 
2. Reiterates strong support for Lebanon's territorial integrity, sovereignty and political independence; 
3. Re-emphasizes the terms of reference and guidelines of the Force as stated in the report of the Secretary-General of 19 March 1978; 
4. Condemns acts of violence against the Force and urges parties to end them; 
5. Reiterates that the Force should fully implement its mandate as defined in resolutions 425 (1978), 426 (1978), and other relevant resolutions; 
6. Encourages efficiency and savings without affecting the Force's operational capacity; 
7. Requests the Secretary-General to continue consultations with Lebanon and other parties and report to the Security Council.
